    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Lensfield Cottage Cambridge</placeName>
                    <date>5<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> Dec<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. 1864</date>
                    <salute>Dear Huxley,</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>There was one expression in my last<ref target="#foot.f1"/> which is not perhaps rigorously exact. Instead of saying “declining to honour it with the Copley Medal of the Royal Society” I should have said simply “not honouring it with the Copley Medal of the Royal Society”<ref target="#foot.f2"/>   For declining implies having been asked, and there was no asking in the present case.</p>
<p>Yours very truly | G. G. Stokes</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
            
            
            
